WorkItem.Description:
Behold:

```
interface IBigComplexInterface {
  lots();
  of();
  methods();
  and();
  stuff();
}

declare class A implements IBigComplexInterface {
  lots();
  of();
  methods();
  and();
  stuff();
}

declare class B implements IBigComplexInterface {
  lots();
  of();
  methods();
  and();
  stuff();
}

declare class C implements IBigComplexInterface {
  lots();
  of();
  methods();
  and();
  stuff();
}

declare class D implements IBigComplexInterface {
  lots();
  of();
  methods();
  and();
  stuff();
}
```

I expected that implemented methods could be implicit for declared classes, which would look like this:

```
interface IBigComplexInterface {
  lots();
  of();
  methods();
  and();
  stuff();
}
declare class A implements IBigComplexInterface {}
declare class B implements IBigComplexInterface {}
declare class C implements IBigComplexInterface {}
declare class D implements IBigComplexInterface {}
```

This adheres to DRY and prevents large amounts of copy/paste when something changes.
